        data-ad-client="ca-pub-5063785223468320"
        data-ad-slot="2509873644"></ins>
    <script>
        (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
    </script>
        
    <div id="use" style="font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; color: #fff; border: 2px solid #fff; padding: 20px; margin: 20px; border-radius: 10px; background-color: #222;">
      <h2>How to Use:</h2>
      <p>1. Click 'Choose an Image' to select an image file.</p>
      <p>2. After choosing a file, click 'Convert' to start the conversion.</p>
      <p>3. Once converted, the ASCII art will be displayed below the button.</p>
      <p>4. Use 'Copy ASCII Art' to copy the art to the clipboard.</p>
  
      <h2>Notes:</h2>
      <p>1. The uploaded image must be in a standard image format (e.g. JPEG, PNG).</p>
      <p>2. The image file size should not exceed the maximum limit.</p>
      <p>3. Depending on the complexity and size of the image, conversion time may vary.</p>
      <p>4. The generated ASCII art is best viewed in a monospaced font.</p>
  
      <h2>Disclaimer:</h2>
      <p>1. This tool is provided as-is, with no guarantees.</p>
      <p>2. The uploaded images are not stored or used for any other purposes.</p>
      <p>3. Ensure you have the rights to use and share the images you upload.</p>
  
      <h2>Privacy:</h2>
      <p>1. Please refer to the <a href="privacy.html" style="color: #ffffff; text-decoration: underline;">privacy policy</a> for more information on data handling.</p>
  </div>

